3:
He forgives all my sins,
\q2 and he heals me from all my diseases;
\q1

7:
Long ago he revealed to Moses what he planned to do;
\q2 he showed to the ancestors of us Israelites the mighty things that he was able to do.
\q1

8:
Yahweh acts mercifully and kindly;
\q2 he does not quickly get angry when we sin;
\q1 he is always showing us that he faithfully loves us.
\q1

15:
We humans do not live forever;
\q2 we are like grass which withers and dies.
\q1 We are like wild flowers that bloom for a short while;
\q1

16:
but then the hot wind blows over them, and they disappear;
\q2 no one sees them again.
\q1

19:
Yahweh has taken his seat in the heavens where he rules as king;
\q2 from there he rules over everything.
\q1
